# Trivy ignores for the Terraform IaC scan.
# Each entry is a deliberate, documented architectural exception — not an
# unreviewed suppression. Everything else is fixed in the modules.

# AWS-0164 — "Subnet associates public IP address."
# The flagged subnets are the PUBLIC subnets, which intentionally assign public
# IPs: they host the NAT gateways and public-facing load balancers (that is the
# definition of a public subnet). All workloads — EKS nodes, Aurora, Redis —
# run in the PRIVATE subnets.
AWS-0164

# AWS-0011 — "Distribution does not utilize a WAF."
# A WAFv2 Web ACL is a separately-managed, billable, per-environment resource.
# The cdn module exposes a `web_acl_id` variable to attach one; it is not
# hardcoded at the module level.
AWS-0011
